//                "description": "<p><strong>Trigger warning:</strong> This episode includes mention of suicidal ideation and mental health struggles. Please listen with care.</p><p><br></p><p>What does it take to finally choose yourself after a lifetime of silence? In this unmissable episode of the Big Gay Overalls podcast, I sit down with the fierce, wise, and wonderfully honest Wendy Cole‚Äîtransgender advocate, speaker, and transition mentor‚Äîwho came out at <em>67 years old</em> and completely rebuilt her life from scratch.</p><p><br></p><p>From facing down psychiatric cruelty in the 1970s, to surviving suicidal ideation, to walking proudly into the world as her full self, Wendy‚Äôs story is not just one of gender identity‚Äîit‚Äôs a masterclass in courage, self-reinvention, and saying, ‚ÄúNo more. I get to be me now.‚Äù</p><p><br></p><p>We dive deep into the emotional, psychological, and social layers of transitioning later in life, why self-awareness and self-acceptance matter more than hormones or presentation, and how she finally found joy, connection, and love on the other side of pain.</p><p><br></p><p>This isn‚Äôt just a conversation about being trans. It‚Äôs a conversation about being <em>human.</em> And if you‚Äôve ever felt like you‚Äôve lived your life at arm‚Äôs length‚Äîlike you‚Äôve been performing someone else&#39;s version of you‚Äîthis one will hit you right in the gut (and then light a fire under it).</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Follow Wendy at:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.meetwendycole.com/\">MeetWendyCole.com</a><br><strong>Wendy‚Äôs Podcast:</strong> <em>Demystifying the Transgender Journey</em> (co-hosted with Lynn Murphy)</p><p><br></p><p>üéß Grab your headphones.
