//                "description": "<p>This episode is a bit of a deep dive, and a long overdue one. I‚Äôve been sitting in a space of reflection lately, trying to make sense of the before and after of my life. Not the shiny, curated ‚Äúbefore and after‚Äù you see in gym photos‚Ä¶ but the emotional, soul-level shift of what happens when you stop living a life that looks good on the outside and start living one that <em>feels</em> right on the inside.</p><p>In this episode, I‚Äôm sharing what it was really like to come out late in life, not just as a lesbian, but as <em>me</em>. What it felt like to live a life that ticked all the boxes but left me feeling empty, bone-tired, and disconnected from my own skin. I talk about the anger I carried, the shame I buried, and the constant push to be someone I wasn‚Äôt‚Ä¶ all in the hope of being accepted.</p><p>But I also talk about the shift. The grief and fear that came with unraveling that life. The slow, quiet moments of stepping into my truth. And the lightness‚Äîoh my god, the <em>relief</em>‚Äîthat followed.</p><p>This is for you if you‚Äôve ever found yourself wondering, ‚ÄúWhat if I built my whole life being someone I‚Äôm not?‚Äù If you‚Äôre in that <em>before</em> stage, where something doesn‚Äôt quite fit and you can‚Äôt unsee it anymore. Or if you‚Äôve already started that journey and you‚Äôre navigating the messy middle. You‚Äôre not too late. You‚Äôre not broken. And you‚Äôre not selfish for wanting more.</p><p>I hope this episode reminds you that you‚Äôre allowed to change. You‚Äôre allowed to grow.
